🍸This Gin Gimlet is a simple yet distinctive cocktail that features a homemade lime cordial & top-notch gin from the UK. Did you know that the UK is the world’s leading gin exporter? @join_jules is using handcrafted @silentpoolgin, which has beautiful floral notes grounded by earthy cassia bark. For this UK-inspired recipe you could also use a Scottish gin such as zesty @edinburghgin or aromatic @caorunngin. Or even a non-alcoholic option from world-leading UK producer @seedlipdrinks. Pair this crisp Gin Gimlet w/ our Scottish Smoked Salmon Tartines! 
👉Discover both of these recipes and more w/ @greatbritishfood by visiting ff.recipes/foodisgreat
#feedfeed #GREATBritishFood #cocktail #gin #gingimlet #unitedkingdom #cocktails #cocktail #happyhour #pairings

This London Fog cocktail features a homemade lavender syrup & frothy vanilla-flavored milk, which fit nicely with @deanstonmalt single malt Scotch Whisky & independent UK tea experts @taylors' Earl Grey Tea. You could also use another single malt Scotch Whisky like @aberlour & @theglenallachie_, or an Irish Whisky like @mcconnellsirishwhisky. This cocktail is the perfect accompaniment to our Chocolate Stout Loaf with Whisky Glaze!
👉Discover this recipe and more w/ @greatbritishfood by visiting ff.recipes/foodisgreat

🥃This Ginger Whisky Smash is the perfect seasonal cocktail! We used fresh plum juice, but this can be substituted for most fruits that may be in season wherever you are located. This recipe uses a classic and beloved jam from the UK, @tiptreephotos Ginger Jam, which pairs perfectly w/ a quality UK Whisky like @penderyn.distillery. You could also use a single malt Scotch like @kilchomanwhisky, a blended whisky like @wemyssmalts or an Irish whiskey such as @bushmillsusa. This cocktail is finished with @fevertreemixers Ginger Beer, a refreshing mixer from the UK. Enjoy this subtly sweet cocktail with an umami-rich bite, like our Muffin Pan Stilton and Chive Popovers!
👉Discover this recipe and more w/ @greatbritishfood by visiting ff.recipes/foodisgreat
